19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Columbus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diego_Columbus\"}, {\"begin\": 413, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 0.9362720671673086, \"rank\": 0.04952190319183227, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer might shock you, or it might not.\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to American two-timegold medalist Lilly King- and others - professional swimmers do urinate in the pool.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 480, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999798457213829, \"rank\": 1.9825655397270215e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\", \"score\": 0.9987997107601976, \"rank\": 0.0010920471968926993, \"text\": \"Lilly\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eli_Lilly_and_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"King, in a recent report byThe Wall Street Journal, told all the dirty details.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.173905122649213e-21, \"text\": \"Wall Street Journal\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Wall_Street_Journal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have probably peed in every single pool I have swam in,\\\"\\u00a0Kingtold the newspaper.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's just how it goes.\\\"\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow Olympians backed up King's claims,saying they dopee in the pool all the time.\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"score\": 0.9274700065052942, \"rank\": 0.02964331818226636, \"text\": \"Fellow\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always have to pee,\\\" Jake Mitchell, who swam for Team USA in Tokyo, toldthe Journal, \\\"because I am so hydrated.\\\"\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9869362169841994, \"rank\": 0.012040127024213823, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9988030763232982, \"rank\": 0.0011054503747095486, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimmers also pointed to the fact that they have to put on their swimsuits at least 20 minutes before a race as a reason for urinating in the pool.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pools are filtered with chemicals, especially chlorine, that protect swimmers from human debris, such as hair, dead skin and urine.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chlorine is used to prevent and kill algae, as well as protect swimmers from unhealthy compounds and waterborne illnesses,according to CNBC.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1263, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlorine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.570129342795396e-30, \"text\": \"Chlorine\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlorine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlorine\"}, {\"begin\": 1398, \"end\": 1402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999997937577731, \"rank\": 1.9620583448077533e-07, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A balanced swimming pool has chlorine levels between 1.0 - 3.0 parts per million, according tothepoolpassion.com.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Over-chlorination can lead to irritated eyes and skin, while not enough chlorine can expose swimmers to unhealthy compounds in the pool from things like human urine.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The more debris that enter the pool, the more chlorine is needed.\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Which is why if you have a pool of your own, it is important to monitor the chlorine levels.\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, peeing in the pool is not recommended.\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1900, \"entities\": []}]}"